their endorsement
today.

07:13.400 --> 07:18.305 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The overwhelming vote means the
accord has
the backing of countries
accounting for 55

07:18.338 --> 07:20.907 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
percent of global emissions,
more than enough.

07:20.940 --> 07:24.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SCHULZ, President,
European Parliament
(through translator): Our vote
opens the way

07:24.277 --> 07:29.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to ensuring that the whole
agreement can achieve
the necessary threshold figures
so as to come

07:29.516 --> 07:31.318 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
into worldwide implementation.

07:31.351 --> 07:36.289 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The E.U.'s member
states are to
make the approval official on
Friday, and

07:36.323 --> 07:37.991 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
present it to the U.N.

07:38.024 --> 07:41.094 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Paris accord formally takes
effect 30
days later.

07:41.127 --> 07:45.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There's a new
surge in the
flow of migrants trying to reach
Italy from

07:45.565 --> 07:47.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Libya.

07:47.334 --> 07:52.305 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
