up and Brown
was hitting in front of Smith.

49:02.039 --> 49:03.174 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Red would ask me, why?

49:03.207 --> 49:07.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the first time he asked me
why, I didn't
know.

49:07.845 --> 49:10.014 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
However, after that, I knew.

49:10.047 --> 49:16.487 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that was part of Red: Be
there early,
be very well-prepared, and then
you're ready

49:16.520 --> 49:17.855 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to go on the air.

49:17.888 --> 49:19.957 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Who are you
talking to when
you're doing the game?

49:19.990 --> 49:23.294 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, you're one of the few
who still does
it alone for the most part.

49:23.327 --> 49:25.729 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So who are you talking to?

49:25.763 --> 49:30.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
VIN SCULLY: Well, first of all,
I have to
make people understand, it's not
an ego thing.

49:30.801 --> 49:33.938 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's not that I just want to be
on all by
myself.

49:33.971 --> 49:41.312 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This goes back to Brooklyn,
where Red's philosophy
was simply this: If I want to
sell you a car,

49:41.345 --> 49:46.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
