you about the
merits of the car or talk to
so-and-so and

49:46.283 --> 49:50.054 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
have you listen to our
discussion about the
merits of the car?

49:50.087 --> 49:53.324 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Red always felt that it was
better to talk
one-on-one.

49:53.357 --> 49:56.293 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So what I'm doing, I'm talking
to the listener.

49:56.327 --> 49:57.528 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And I will talk.

49:57.561 --> 49:59.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I will say, oh, by the way, I
forgot to tell
you, or...

49:59.363 --> 50:01.098 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: I forgot to tell
you.

50:01.131 --> 50:04.435 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
VIN SCULLY: Exactly, talking --
because I
don't want the microphone to be
in the way.

50:04.468 --> 50:07.738 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I want them to know I'm sitting
next to them
in the ballpark talking.

50:07.771 --> 50:11.408 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Yankee Stadium shivering in its
concrete foundation
right now.

50:11.442 --> 50:16.647 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: He called the
only perfect
game pitched in a World Series,
Don Larsen's

50:16.680 --> 50:19.850 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
gem for the Yankees against the
Brooklyn Dodgers
in 1956.

50:19.884 --> 50:21.252 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
VIN SCULLY: Got him!

50:21.285 --> 50:27.725 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The greatest game ever pitched
in baseball
history by Don Larsen!

50:27.758 --> 50:33.297 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Nine years later,
Scully was
there for Sandy Koufax's perfect
game.

50:33.330 --> 50:36.667 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
VIN SCULLY: Sandy into his
windup.

50:36.700 --> 50:39.536 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Here's the pitch.

50:39.570 --> 50:41.405 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Swung on and missed! ha perfect
game!

50:41.438 --> 50:42.773 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
